# Crate async_h1Copy item path
[Settings](https://docs.rs/async-h1/latest/settings.html)
[Help](https://docs.rs/async-h1/latest/help.html)
Summary[Source](https://docs.rs/async-h1/latest/src/async_h1/lib.rs.html#1-137)
Expand description
Streaming async HTTP 1.1 parser.
At its core HTTP is a stateful RPC protocol, where a client and server communicate with one another by encoding and decoding messages between them.
  * `client` encodes HTTP requests, and decodes HTTP responses.
  * `server` decodes HTTP requests, and encodes HTTP responses.


A client always starts the HTTP connection. The lifetime of an HTTP connection looks like this:
```
1. encode      2. decode
    \      /
    -> request ->
 client        server
    <- response <-
    /      \
4. decode      3. encode
```

See also [`async-tls`](https://docs.rs/async-tls), [`async-std`](https://docs.rs/async-std).
## [§](https://docs.rs/async-h1/latest/async_h1/#example)Example
**HTTP client**
```
use async_std::net::TcpStream;
use http_types::{Method, Request, Url};
#[async_std::main]
async fn main() -> http_types::Result<()> {
  let stream = TcpStream::connect("127.0.0.1:8080").await?;
  let peer_addr = stream.peer_addr()?;
  println!("connecting to {}", peer_addr);
  let url = Url::parse(&format!("http://{}/foo", peer_addr))?;
  let req = Request::new(Method::Get, url);
  let res = async_h1::connect(stream.clone(), req).await?;
  println!("{:?}", res);
  Ok(())
}
```

**HTTP Server**
```
use async_std::net::{TcpStream, TcpListener};
use async_std::prelude::*;
use async_std::task;
use http_types::{Response, StatusCode};
#[async_std::main]
async fn main() -> http_types::Result<()> {
  // Open up a TCP connection and create a URL.
  let listener = TcpListener::bind(("127.0.0.1", 8080)).await?;
  let addr = format!("http://{}", listener.local_addr()?);
  println!("listening on {}", addr);
  // For each incoming TCP connection, spawn a task and call `accept`.
  let mut incoming = listener.incoming();
  while let Some(stream) = incoming.next().await {
    let stream = stream?;
    task::spawn(async {
      if let Err(err) = accept(stream).await {
        eprintln!("{}", err);
      }
    });
  }
  Ok(())
}
// Take a TCP stream, and convert it into sequential HTTP request / response pairs.
async fn accept(stream: TcpStream) -> http_types::Result<()> {
  println!("starting new connection from {}", stream.peer_addr()?);
  async_h1::accept(stream.clone(), |_req| async move {
    let mut res = Response::new(StatusCode::Ok);
    res.insert_header("Content-Type", "text/plain");
    res.set_body("Hello");
    Ok(res)
  })
  .await?;
  Ok(())
}
```

## Re-exports[§](https://docs.rs/async-h1/latest/async_h1/#reexports)

`pub use client::connect[](https://docs.rs/async-h1/latest/async_h1/client/fn.connect.html "fn async_h1::client::connect");`


`pub use server::accept[](https://docs.rs/async-h1/latest/async_h1/server/fn.accept.html "fn async_h1::server::accept");`


`pub use server::accept_with_opts[](https://docs.rs/async-h1/latest/async_h1/server/fn.accept_with_opts.html "fn async_h1::server::accept_with_opts");`


`pub use server::ServerOptions[](https://docs.rs/async-h1/latest/async_h1/server/struct.ServerOptions.html "struct async_h1::server::ServerOptions");`

## Modules[§](https://docs.rs/async-h1/latest/async_h1/#modules)

[client](https://docs.rs/async-h1/latest/async_h1/client/index.html "mod async_h1::client")
    Process HTTP connections on the client.

[server](https://docs.rs/async-h1/latest/async_h1/server/index.html "mod async_h1::server")
    Process HTTP connections on the server.
## Macros[§](https://docs.rs/async-h1/latest/async_h1/#macros)

[read_to_end](https://docs.rs/async-h1/latest/async_h1/macro.read_to_end.html "macro async_h1::read_to_end")
    like ready! but early-returns the Poll<Result> early in all situations other than Ready(Ok(0))

